p: Fraction F 1 (0.5 g) was subjected to preparative TLC (normal phase) to obtain compound 1 (0.230 g, Figure 4). Fraction F 2 (0.5 g) was also subjected to preparative TLC (reversed phase) to obtain fraction F 2a (0.2102 g), an intractable mixture. Fraction F 3 (0.5 g) was further purified using semi-preparative HPLC to yield compound 2 (0.019 g). Fraction F 4 (0.5 g) was also subjected to preparative TLC (reversed phase) to obtain compound 3 (0.1238 g). F 5 (1 g) was further purified using semi-preparative HPLC to obtain compound 4 (0.086 g). Compounds 1 [ 25], 2 [ 28], 3 [ 27], and 4 [ 27] are known compounds.
